{
    "analysis": "We inspected metrics, traces, and logs for IG01 in the incident window. Findings so far: 1) Metric-level scan across all components flagged several strong anomalies starting at ~18:00–18:01, with IG01 OSLinux-CPU_CPU_CPUWio and IG01 CPU-related KPIs among the highest breach ratios. 2) Trace-level scan for the top candidate nodes shows pronounced high-latency anomalies originating from IG01 and IG02 starting at 18:00 (multiple trace.self.duration_p95 and trace.to_Tomcat*.duration_p95 series show early high values). 3) The IG01 telemetry extract contains many metric points (we returned 50 metric rows filtered to CPUWio/CPULoad/CPUSysTime) and 100 trace rows; no log or error_logs rows were found for IG01 in the window. Interpretation: IG01 exhibits both severe metric deviations (high CPU WIO) and immediate trace-level latency spikes at the start of the window, making it a prime root-cause candidate. However, to localize the root cause we must identify a true 'fault' sub-series (consecutive anomalies) rather than isolated spikes and determine the exact first occurrence timestamp. We also need to confirm the fault severity (breach ratio relative to global P95) and rule out simultaneous upstream/backend faults. Therefore we must detect consecutive anomalies (filtering out isolated spikes) in IG01 CPU-related KPIs using global thresholds computed from the full series, and report earliest fault timestamps and severity. No IG01 logs are available to further refine the resource reason, so metrics + traces are our primary evidence.",
